191.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News examines whether the shooting of a teenage boy by police will be a turning point in President Rodrigo Duterte's war on drugs.

192.plot: [HBO] HD. As a judge temporarily blocked enforcement of Senate Bill 4, VICE News examines the controversial immigration policy.

193.plot: [HBO] HD. As the Trump administration announces plans to rescind DACA, VICE News talks with an immigration lawyer who is himself a DACA recipient.

194.plot: [HBO] HD. As Texans reckon with Harvey's fallout, Roberto Ferdman looks at what happened when officials ordered a second flood to save the city.

197.title: Episode #1.197
197.plot: [HBO] HD. In Hurricane Harvey's wake, Houston residents are dealing with one of the storm's biggest hangovers: eight million cubic yards of debris.

198.title: Rohingya Refugees & Riding Out Irma
198.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News sat down with a family that chose not to evacuate from Hurricane Irma's path.

199.plot: [HBO] HD. After the Trump administration's DACA announcement, VICE News followed a Dreamer as she figured out how to pull her life back together.

200.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News travels to St. Louis to report on the protests sparked by former police officer Jason Stockley's acquittal of killing a suspect.

201.plot: [HBO] HD. Three months into the offensive to retake the ISIS stronghold of Raqqa, VICE News travels to the city to witness the battle firsthand.

202.plot: [HBO] HD. Nigel Duara learns more about the possibility of extinction for jaguars, who are being threatened by Trump's proposed border wall.

203.plot: [HBO] HD. GOES-16, a new satellite launched by the NOAA has been producing the most detailed hurricane images ever recorded.

204.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News talks to one of the evangelist missionaries pushing to keep solar energy in Indiana.

205.plot: [HBO] HD. Today marks the 3rd anniversary of the disappearance of 43 Mexican college students in Iguala, but going missing in Mexico isn't uncommon.

206.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News visits a coal country activist documenting mining activities that he believes are polluting the environment.

207.plot: [HBO] HD. Controversy arose when it was announced the Kurdish independence vote includes areas claimed by both the federal and regional governments.

208.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News follows San Juan police during an overnight shift to see what happens after curfew.

209.plot: [HBO] HD. Roberto Ferdman talks to federal employees in San Juan who say there aren't enough people on the ground to get everyone the help they need.

210.plot: [HBO] HD. VICE News travels to Alaska to visit HAARP, a military-built facility shrouded in conspiracy theories.

211.plot: [HBO] HD. Prototypes for Trump's border wall are hard to see from the American side but a photographer has discovered a vantage from Mexico's side.

-1.title: Roseanne, Interrupted: An intimate portrait of Roseanne Barr after the tweet that got her fired
-1.plot: In an new, exclusive interview with VICE News Tonight on HBO, Roseanne Barr, creator of the 'Roseanne' show, opens up about her life since she was fired by ABC for her Tweet about former aide to President Obama, Valerie Jarrett.

imdb.title: Vice News Tonight
plot: A nightly news show Monday through Friday. Discusses current global issues and various news topics.::Tuesday Grace Sinclair
